[center][size=6][b]ReShade HDR Installer[/b][/size]
[size=3]A desktop manager for HDR game mods on Windows. Auto-detects your game libraries, installs ReShade, RenoDX, ReLimiter, Display Commander, OptiScaler, RE Framework, and Luma Framework mods all in a few clicks.[/size][/center]

[line]

[color=FF6644][b]Disclaimer[/b][/color]
RHI is an unofficial third-party tool, not affiliated with or endorsed by the RenoDX project, Crosire, or the Luma Framework. All mod files are downloaded from their official sources at runtime and are not redistributed.

[color=FF4444][b] Single-player only[/b][/color]
RHI installs ReShade with full addon support, which may be flagged by anti-cheat in online/multiplayer games. Uninstall ReShade before playing online.

[line]

[size=5][b]Acknowledgements[/b][/size]
ReShade HDR Installer would not be possible without the hard work of the entire RenoDX team and [url=https://reshade.me]Crosire[/url], the creator of ReShade. Their dedication to open-source HDR modding is what makes tools like this one viable. Thank you to every mod author, contributor, and tester who keeps pushing PC HDR forward.

[line]

[size=5][b]Download[/b][/size]
Grab the latest installer from the [url=https://github.com/RankFTW/RHI/releases]Releases page[/url]. Requires Windows 10/11 x64 and [url=https://dotnet.microsoft.com/download/dotnet/8.0].NET 8 Desktop Runtime[/url].

[line]

[size=5][b]Quick Start[/b][/size]
[list=1]
[*] [b]Run ReShade HDR Installer[/b] — games are auto-detected from Steam, GOG, Epic, EA App, Ubisoft, Xbox Game Pass, Battle.net, and Rockstar on every launch.
[*] [b]Pick a game[/b] from the sidebar. Use search or filter chips to narrow the list.
[*] [b]Install components[/b] from the detail panel — ReShade, RenoDX, and a frame rate limiter (ReLimiter or Display Commander) each have a one-click install button.
[*] [b]Launch the game[/b], press [b]Home[/b] to open ReShade, go to the [b]Add-ons[/b] tab, and configure RenoDX.
[/list]

[line]

[size=5][b]Features[/b][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]8-store game detection[/b] — Steam, GOG, Epic, EA App, Ubisoft Connect, Xbox Game Pass, Battle.net, Rockstar. New games appear automatically on every launch.
[*] [b]Graphics API detection[/b] — scans game executables via PE header analysis to detect DirectX 8–12, Vulkan, and OpenGL. API badges shown on game cards. Results cached to disk for fast subsequent launches.
[*] [b]Vulkan ReShade support[/b] — installs ReShade as a global Vulkan implicit layer for Vulkan-rendered games, with per-game INI and shader deployment.
[*] [b]One-click install/update/uninstall[/b] for ReShade, ReLimiter, Display Commander, OptiScaler, RenoDX addons, RE Framework, and Luma Framework mods.
[*] [b]Frame rate limiter choice[/b] — ReLimiter and Display Commander are mutually exclusive per game. Installing one disables the other. Both support 32-bit and 64-bit games.
[*] [b]Display Commander support[/b] — install and manage the Display Commander (LITE) frame rate limiter per-game, downloaded from GitHub on demand with automatic update detection. Includes INI deploy button.
[*] [b]OptiScaler support[/b] — install and manage OptiScaler per-game for upscaler redirection (DLSS/FSR/XeSS). Handles DLL naming (auto-selects winmm.dll for Vulkan games), INI configuration, ReShade coexistence (automatic rename to ReShade64.dll), GPU type settings (NVIDIA/AMD/Intel), DLSS input toggle (AMD/Intel only), and hotkey setup. Automatically downloads and deploys the latest DLSS Super Resolution, Ray Reconstruction, and Frame Generation DLLs. OptiPatcher auto-deployed for AMD/Intel GPUs. 64-bit games only.
[*] [b]ReShade dependency enforcement[/b] — RenoDX, ReLimiter, and Display Commander require ReShade to be installed first. Install buttons show "ReShade required" when ReShade is not present.
[*] [b]DLSS auto-download[/b] — the latest NVIDIA DLSS Super Resolution, Ray Reconstruction, and Frame Generation DLLs are automatically downloaded and deployed to game folders on OptiScaler install.
[*] [b]OptiPatcher[/b] — automatically downloaded and deployed for AMD/Intel GPU users during OptiScaler install, enabling DLSS inputs without GPU spoofing.
[*] [b]Mass INI Deployment[/b] — deploy reshade.ini, relimiter.ini, DisplayCommander.ini, or OptiScaler.ini to all games with the corresponding component installed from the Settings page.
[*] [b]Mass ReShade Preset Install[/b] — deploy presets to multiple games at once from the Settings page, with optional shader pack installation.
[*] [b]ReLimiter support[/b] — install and manage the ReLimiter frame pacing addon per-game, downloaded from GitHub on demand with automatic update detection.
[*] [b]RE Framework support[/b] — one-click install, update, and uninstall of RE Framework for RE Engine games (Monster Hunter Wilds, Resident Evil series, Devil May Cry 5, Street Fighter 6, Dragon's Dogma 2, etc.). Each game downloads its own game-specific build.
[*] [b]Version display[/b] — installed version numbers shown directly on component rows. DC version reads from PE file info on scan.
[*] [b]Shader pack management[/b] — 41 HDR shader packs with global and per-game shader selection, plus a Custom mode for user shader directories. Shader packs can declare dependencies (e.g. Azen auto-selects smolbbsoop shaders).
[*] [b]ReShade addon management[/b] — browse and toggle curated ReShade addons from the official list via the Addon Manager. Toggling on downloads the addon automatically, toggling off disables deployment but keeps files cached. Addons are auto-deployed when ReShade is installed, removed when ReShade is uninstalled, and synced on every Refresh. Per-game addon overrides let you customise which addons are active per game.
[*] [b]Nexus Mods & PCGamingWiki links[/b] — each game shows clickable Nexus Mods and PCGW buttons in the detail panel, resolved automatically from the public game catalogue and Steam AppID lookup. Games that can't be matched automatically can be overridden in the manifest.
[*] [b]ReShade preset deployment[/b] — place .ini preset files in the reshade-presets folder and deploy them to any game from the overrides panel, or drag-and-drop a preset .ini onto RHI to deploy it with automatic shader pack installation.
[*] [b]ReShade Without Addon Support[/b] — per-game toggle to switch from addon-enabled ReShade to standard ReShade. All addons are removed and rows dimmed; toggle back to restore.
[*] [b]ReLimiter OSD hotkey[/b] — configure the ReLimiter overlay hotkey from the Settings page and apply it to all managed relimiter.ini files.
[*] [b]Automatic INI deploy on first install[/b] — installing ReLimiter or Display Commander for the first time auto-copies the pre-configured INI from AppData to the game folder (only if not already present).
[*] [b]Game report[/b] — Copy Report button in the overrides panel generates a diagnostic code for Discord or GitHub issues, showing detected vs corrected settings with an optional user note.
[*] [b]Auto-save overrides[/b] — all per-game settings save immediately when changed, no Save button needed.
[*] [b]Per-game overrides[/b] — DLL naming overrides (single toggle for both ReShade and DC), shader mode/selection, wiki name mapping, wiki exclusion, Update Inclusion button with colour-coded summary (ReShade, RenoDX, ReLimiter, DC, OptiScaler), bitness and graphics API overrides (side by side), reset overrides.
[*] [b]Seamless refresh[/b] — after initial boot, refresh updates everything in the background without blanking the UI.
[*] [b]Startup shader deployment[/b] — on launch, shaders are automatically synced to all installed game folders in parallel for fast startup.
[*] [b]Drag-and-drop[/b] — drop a game .exe to add it, drop an .addon64/.addon32 to install it, drop an archive to extract and install addons, drop a preset .ini to deploy it with automatic shader install, or drop a Discord/browser URL link to download and install an addon.
[*] [b]Archive auto-install[/b] — the watch folder detects .zip, .7z, and .rar archives containing "renodx" in the filename (e.g. from Nexus Mods downloads) and automatically extracts and installs the addon files inside.
[*] [b]Remote manifest[/b] — game-specific overrides updated server-side without app releases, including engine overrides, DLL name overrides, API overrides, and DC mode overrides.
[*] [b]UE-Extended / Native HDR[/b] — automatic detection and addon assignment for Unreal Engine games.
[*] [b]Engine detection[/b] — Unreal, Unity, RE Engine, and custom engine names detected and displayed with icons.
[*] [b]ReShadePreset.ini auto-deploy[/b] — place a preset in the RHI inis folder and it will be copied to every game install automatically.
[*] [b]Foreign DLL protection[/b] — detects DXVK, Special K, ENB, etc. before overwriting.
[*] [b]Auto-update[/b] — checks for new RHI versions on launch with stable and beta channels.
[*] [b]Settings page[/b] — shader mode, deploy actions, preferences, logs, and credits all in one place.
[*] [b]About page[/b] — app description, credits & acknowledgements, disclaimers, and links accessible from the Help flyout.
[*] [b]Addon auto-detection[/b] — watches your Downloads folder for new renodx-*.addon64 / .addon32 files and archives, and prompts you to install them. Configurable watch folder in Settings.
[*] [b]AddonPath support[/b] — addon installs respect the AddonPath setting in reshade.ini, deploying addons to the configured folder instead of the game root.
[*] [b]Luma author badges[/b] — games in Luma mode show the Luma mod author (from the Luma wiki) in place of the RenoDX author badge.
[*] [b]Filter mode persistence[/b] — your selected filter tab is saved and automatically restored when you reopen the app.
[*] [b]Custom filter chips[/b] — save any search query as a named filter chip. Custom chips use a teal colour scheme and persist across sessions.
[*] [b]Universal keyword search[/b] — search by store, engine, graphics API, bitness, mod name, mod author, and more.
[*] [b]Skeleton loading screen[/b] — animated placeholder shapes mimic the real layout while the app loads.
[*] [b]Screenshot path settings[/b] — set a global screenshot save path written to all managed reshade.ini files, with optional per-game subfolders.
[*] [b]Toolbar redesign[/b] — consistent teal accent styling with grouped sections. Update All button lights up purple when updates are available.
[*] [b]Clickable status links[/b] — version numbers and author donation badges show a hand cursor when clickable. DC status text is underlined when installed.
[*] [b]Performance optimisations[/b] — parallel shader pack downloads, parallel game folder syncs, PE-level and game-level API caching, WindowsApps path skipping, debounced PCGW cache writes, optimised DLL scanning, DLC blacklisting. Full Refresh clears all caches.
[/list]

[line]

[size=5][b]Troubleshooting[/b][/size]
[list]
[*] [b]Game not detected?[/b] Click [b]Add Game[/b] in Settings or drag the game's .exe onto the window.
[*] [b]Xbox games missing?[/b] Click Refresh — RHI uses the PackageManager API.
[*] [b]ReShade not loading?[/b] Check the install path via the folder icon — dxgi.dll must be next to the game exe.
[*] [b]Black screen (Unreal)?[/b] ReShade → Add-ons → RenoDX → set R10G10B10A2UNORM to output size.
[*] [b]UE-Extended not working?[/b] Turn on in-game HDR — UE-Extended requires native HDR output.
[*] [b]Downloads failing?[/b] Click Refresh, or clear cache from Settings → Open Downloads Cache.
[*] [b]Foreign DLL blocking install?[/b] Choose Overwrite in the dialog, or cancel to keep the existing file.
[*] [b]Games/mods out of sync?[/b] Settings → Full Refresh to clear all caches.
[/list]

For detailed documentation on shader packs, Luma Framework, Display Commander, per-game overrides, game detection methods, and more, see the [url=https://github.com/RankFTW/RenoDXChecker]Detailed Guide[/url].

